<p class="headline"><a href="http://www.boingboing.net/2011/05/30/mexico-kindergarten.html" rel="bookmark">Mexico: kindergarten teacher keeps class calm with song as narco gun massacre rages outside</a></p>
<p class="byline" style="text-align:left">
<a class="names" href="http://www.boingboing.net/author/xeni-jardin/">Xeni Jardin</a> at 10:33 PM Monday, May 30, 2011&nbsp;<a href="http://boingboing.net/submit"><img src="http://boingboing.net/style/bug.png" style="margin-bottom:-2px;"></a><span style="float:right;"></span>


<p>	
		
<p><object width="600" height="480"><param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube-nocookie.com/v/I7vjig6UlFg?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US"></param><param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"></param><param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"></param><embed src="http://www.youtube-nocookie.com/v/I7vjig6UlFg?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" width="600" height="480" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true"></embed></object><p>
Boing Boing reader <a href="http://boingboing.net/submit/2011/05/mexican-kindergarten-teacher-leads-class-in-song-while-massacre-happens-outside.html">GIFtheory says</a>, "This video of a kindergarten teacher [near Monterrey, Mexico] beseeching her students to keep their heads on the floor while leading them in song is simultaneously the most horrifying and inspirational thing I've seen in a while." <p><a href="http://youtu.be/I7vjig6UlFg">Video Link</a>.<p> <em><small>(via <a href="http://www.boingboing.net/submit/">BB Submitterator</a>)</small></em>

